---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
import SectionIntro from "../components/SectionIntro.astro";
import PageContainer from "../components/PageContainer.astro";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";


const title = "Social Media";
const description =
  "Social media guidelines for Mikkeller Running Club. Learn how to communicate consistently, responsibly, and creatively across all MRC chapters.";
const currentPage = "social-media";
---

<Layout {title} {description} {currentPage}>
  <PageHeader pageNumber="08" heading="Social\nMedia" />
   <PageContainer>
   <SectionIntro
    text="Social media helps us share the spirit of MRC with the world. To keep our community consistent and recognisable, please follow these simple guidelines when you post."
  />
<h2>Guidelines</h2>
 <div class="two-columns section ">
    <p>
      To increase our overall presence and engagement, we encourage everyone to be active on social media. Please create the following profiles and share the links with us: <br>
       <span class="bold-text">Facebook</span> <br>
       <span class="bold-text">Instagram</span> <br>

These platforms help us communicate updates, present activities, and engage with our community. <br><br>To ensure clear communication and easy access to important details, please make sure the following elements are visible and up to date. <br><br> As a craft beer–based community, we take our communication seriously. We do not allow content that: <br><br>
       <span class="bold-text">- Targets or demeans minorities </span> <br>
        <span class="bold-text">- Includes sexual, pornographic, or suggestive material</span> <br>
         <span class="bold-text">- Content promoting external products, events, or brands without prior approval  </span> <br>
          <span class="bold-text">- Posts that are repetitive, irrelevant, or automated</span> <br>  



    </p>

    <p>

      <span class="bold-text"> FAQ About MRC</span> <br>  
     
You should include an accessible FAQ section where new and existing members can quickly find answers to common questions about MRC. You can find the FAQ here: [insert link] <br><br>


<span class="bold-text">Weekly Practice Schedule</span> <br>  

Make sure your weekly practice details are clearly displayed, including: <br>
<span class="bold-text">Practice times</span> <br>  
<span class="bold-text">Teams/groups</span> <br>  
<span class="bold-text">Meeting point/location</span> <br>  
    </p>
  </div>



  <div class="grey_box">
  <h2>templates</h2>
  <div class="two-columns">
    <div>
    <p>
    We encourage you to be creative, but we also want to help you show the best of the best from your runs. That is why we created templates and gathered them for your and some of our favorites in this guide. <br><br>
    To ensure a consistent and professional visual identity across all teams and communication channels, please make use of our official Figma Guide. <br><br>

    <span class="bold-text">The guide includes</span> <br>  
    
- Brand colors and typography <br>
- Logos and graphic elements <br>
- Templates for social media posts <br>
- Layout guidelines for announcements and updates <br> <br>
Make sure to review the Figma Guide before creating any visual materials, so all content aligns with our overall branding.
    </p>
    </div>
    
    <div>
  <img src="/img/templates.png" alt="MRC Logo Example" />
   <Button href="/kontakt" label="download" />

    </div>
  </div>
  </div>



<div class="text-row">
  <h2>Don’ts:</h2>
  <p>
   Do not alter, weaken, or reduce our brand’s colors, typography, or visual features. Always follow the original MRC style or your chapter’s approved style — and avoid any treatments that compromise the integrity or clarity of the identity.
  </p>
</div>


<div class="grid_1_1_1 section">
  <div class="sm-image"><img src="/img/sm-1.png" alt="" /></div>
  <div class="sm-image"><img src="/img/sm-2.png" alt="" /></div>
  <div class="sm-image"><img src="/img/sm-3.png" alt="" /></div>
</div>




</PageContainer>
</Layout>

<style>
  .two-columns img {
   width: 100%;
  }

 .two-columns div:last-child {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center; /* centrer horisontalt */
}
/* WRAPPER */
.sm-image {
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;
  border-radius: 8px;
  display: block;

  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateY(30px);
  transition: opacity 0.8s ease, transform 0.8s ease;
}

/* Når de scroller ind */
.sm-image.visible {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateY(0);
}

/* IMAGE EFFECT */
.sm-image img {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  display: block;

  transition:
    transform 0.4s ease,
    box-shadow 0.4s ease;
}

/* Hover effect */
.sm-image:hover img {
  transform: scale(1.04);
  box-shadow: 0px 12px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18);
}

/* Underline i dine 3 farver */
.sm-image::after {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  bottom: -5px;
  left: 0;
  width: 0%;
  height: 4px;

  background: linear-gradient(
    90deg,
    #214082,
    #d6b3d5,
    #badeb9
  );

  border-radius: 2px;
  transition: width 0.4s ease;
}

.sm-image:hover::after {
  width: 100%;
}


</style>

<script>
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
      if (entry.isIntersecting) entry.target.classList.add('visible');
    });
  });

  document.querySelectorAll('.image-box, .sm-image')
    .forEach(el => observer.observe(el));
</script>
 